Surveys of avian diversity were performed at 61 sites across the Mojave Desert spanning a broad latitudinal (33.6° to 37.5°), longitudinal (−117.7° to −114.8°), and elevational range (−17.8 to 3396.2 m) (
 
  SI Appendix, Fig. S1
 ). The majority of sites (58 of 61) were on federal lands managed by the NPS, US Bureau of Land Management (BLM), US Forest Service (USFS), and US Fish and Wildlife Service (
 
  SI Appendix, Fig. S1
 ). Only one site experienced development from the historic time period; resurvey of this site occurred <1 km away in habitat matching historic descriptions.
